==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Trencher-man
<hw>Trench"er-man</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Trencher-men</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A feeder; a great eater; a gormandizer.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A cook.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The skillfulest <qex>trencher-men</qex> of Media.</q> <rj><qau>Sir
P. Sidney.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A table companion; a trencher mate.</def>
<rj><au>Thackeray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trenchmore</ent>⟦br⟧
